(362, 1867, 222, 121, '1', 'upload/222//customer_profile_document/xkD9m2ZtvN0f8nxHVHUZc3gbrt638lProject_grant_2.pdf', 'WombSpace', 'The WombSpace is a condensed experience of the cosmos” An expansive experience that uses the latest projection and sound, experience design technology and AI as healing tools.\r\nThe WombSpace is Van Goghs’ starry night in the most futuristic way. The WombSpace is an otherworldly habitat that brings the human back to the universe.\r\nA moving space, an art piece in constant creation, that invites us to just be and experience the beauty of limitless imagination and connection with our soul and each other.\r\nMartin Buber describes prenatal life as the original state of ecstatic consciousness within a sexual-spiritual universe, “a flowing toward each other, a bodily reciprocity.” The mother’s womb is a condensed experience of the cosmos. At birth we forget this undivided world, but we never forget completely. The memory lingers as a “secret image of a wish,” a desire for total reintegration, and this is the real meaning of the human longing to return to the womb. It is not at all a sign of pathology or inadequacy, not a backward craving, but an urge to expand, to reestablish the cosmic connection.\r\nThe “THE WOMB-SPACE\" (a form of egg shape) will be connected to other WOMB-SPACES. I envision a jungle of WOMB-SPACES that are interconnected. Picture the Matrix and its interconnected “boxes”, however, a jungle, a paradise of beauty and light. NATURE. The human being experiences on its own, but the collective experience will be documented and translated into knowledge feeding the AI system, the manifestation, and creating reality.\r\nEach journey will start by balancing the energetic levels in the body through vibration and sounds (sound healing), followed by an orchestra of sensations, an individual experience of awakening the body and mind with all senses. Our surroundings shape the way we think. Where you are matters. Someone in Alaska sees the colors differently than someone in LA. If we spin this thought further and if we see our mico-organism as part of the whole (“everything and all at once”), it just makes sense that the way we receive feelings and messages, changes from our geographical standpoint. These differences in experiencing the world bring us together or apart.', 0, 1, '2023-03-17 23:01:19', '2023-03-17 23:02:17'),
